docs/guides/01-getting-started.md
     1→# Getting Started
     2→
     3→## Installing Superstruct
     4→
     5→To install Superstruct run:
     6→
     7→```bash
     8→npm install --save superstruct
     9→```
    10→
    11→And then you can import it:
    12→
    13→```ts
    14→import { object, string, number } from 'superstruct'
    15→
    16→const User = object({
    17→  id: number(),
    18→  name: string(),
    19→})
    20→```
    21→
    22→If you'd like, you can use a wildcard import:
    23→
    24→```ts
    25→import * as s from 'superstruct'
    26→
    27→const User = s.object({
    28→  id: s.number(),
    29→  name: s.string(),
    30→})
    31→```
    32→
    33→If you'd rather use a `<script>` tag, you can use the UMD build:
    34→
    35→```html
    36→<script src="https://unpkg.com/superstruct/lib/index.cjs"></script>
    37→```
    38→
    39→This will expose the `Superstruct` global.
    40→
